        "page": "11",
        "text": "LLC 1.949.544.5208 Wed Aug 18 45:59:55 2010 \u00a5 zFrom Urban West Ventures, * Acquisition Summary - Five Points Car Wash- 12604 Whittier Boulevard, Whittier, California Contract Purchase Price $3,200,000 This document is intended as a brief overview for the Acquisition of the Five Points Car Wash in Whittier. For more detail, please contact either Mike Shullman at 203-249-2694 or Stewart Winkler at 949-278-1002. INTRODUCTION The 5 Points Car Wash located in Whittier, California (hereinafter the \u201cProperty\u201d) is an exceptional acquisition and rehabilitation opportunity for a seasoned car wash operator. \u2018The site is located on an intersection of five streets which has more than 80,000 cars per day of traffic and, as a result of a historically unique and unusually large pole mounted street sign, superior visibility (see the attached maps and recent articles are available upon request). The Property is 2.82 acres comprised of the car wash tunnel and ancillary car wash uses including a retail center and detail bays, a 1,800 square foot free-standing retail building, three industrial buildings totaling 14,000 square feet, and a fenced-in surface parking area which is currently rented. (see the attached site plan) The Property is in a high density area which includes approximately 30,000 people in one mile, 162,000 people in 3 miles and 437,000 in 5 miles. Average household income is approximately $65,000, which is good for the pricing points for the services to be offered at the wash. Additionally, while car washes in the local vicinity exist, there is a lack of competition for the proposed pricing and service model: the five-dollar, five-minute car wash. While no recent appraisal has been conducted, the value of comparable for sale retail and industrial properties in close proximity to the site indicate a conservative land value with improvements of between $3,600,000 and $4,500,000 in its existing condition. However, all of the comparable properties for sale used to estimate a value have inferior locations relative to the Five Points Car Wash when compared on traffic count and proximity to a hard comer. As a result of the mismanagement of the car wash business and adjacent commercial property, profits declined, the seller defaulted on their mortgage and day-to-day operations were taken back by a court appointed receiver. Originally offered for sale at $5.8 million, M"
