        "text": "Marketing and Promotions cont. Super Star is the first major car wash chain to develop a mobile app with industry leader DRB Systems. Over 58,000 users have the ability to prepay for washes through the app and redeem points for a free wash. As mentioned above, the app will be undergoing a redesign/refresh in the later part of 2021 to further improve the user experience. Social Media In the rapidly changing landscape of social media, the Company has kept pace with the consumer by tailoring its messaging in order to resonate. Transitioning from giveaways and contests to a more holistic approach, the Company has constructed a strategic social media calendar to engage followers through car wash education, promotions, employee and community recognition, and human interest. Facebook followers exceed 14,000, Instagram followers exceed 8,600, and the Company recently launched digital targeting to grow its YouTube following. Super Star is also exploring the use of influencers in mediums such as Tik Tok along with lnstagram and Facebook. Community Partnerships The Company strategically partners with various corporations, charities, businesses and first responders in Arizona and California. It also is a proud sponsor of various local schools and youth activity groups. In doing so, Super Star is able to create personal relationships within the community and increase brand awareness while giving back. This year, Super Star is engaging in major partnerships with Phoenix Children's Hospital to sponsor Child Car Seat Safety Week, as well as with Paul's Car Wash to support Big Brothers/Big Sisters of Arizona and KUPD to provide resources to 1,000 of Arizona's deployed troops. Super Star uses newspaper advertising when the opportunity strategically aligns with the current marketing plan. One such opportunity arose recently with the Arizona Republic, the state's flagship newspaper. The Company placed strategic ads after being nominated as one of 2021's \"Best of the Desert\". As of writing, the Company has been informed it is a finalist in both the Central and East Valley with the winners being announced mid-May 2021. 2021 wore NB fathers I\u00b1Marni 891 Sisters OCTOBER 19-23 VIRTUAL FUNDRAISER PURCHASE A \u2022 PAIRS WASH' AT SUPER STAR CAR WASH S SOT.Val BE DONATED TEXT PCW20 TO ta, OR DONATE AT 112F/INGA Strictly Private and Confidential 30"
