        "page": "199",
        "text": "Financial Summary Income Statements Financial Statement Overview Super Star has exhibited strong income statement trends while maintaining a solid balance sheet foundation to further expand. The results seen here are summarized on a consolidated basis, with financials for the SS Holding and corporate entities combined with those of the Arizona and California sites. Day-to-day business is run on an accrual basis and financial reporting operates on a calendar year basis, with Microsoft Dynamics 365 used as the Company's accounting software. Historical financials have been reviewed by independent accountant BeachFleischman PC, and starting in 2020 the Company has tapped the same firm for audit services. Income Statement Summary The Company's income statements showcase strong top line and bottom line performance. Primary revenue generator Car Wash sales, which includes both membership revenues as well as pay-per-wash sales, experienced 32.6% growth between 2019 and 2020, and a few months later, grew another 20.6% from 2020 to the 2021 LTM period through May. The only revenue line which has declined materially since 2019 is Fuel, a result of market gasoline prices, and which is not a significant profit center for the business. Note that beginning in March 2019, Management raised the base wash price from $3.00 to $5.00, and thus 2019 results reflect a mix of price points. Base washes are now up to $6.00 in Arizona, while in California the base pricing is $7.00 to $9.00. Even with these price increases the Company. is not losing volume, and anticipates further price increases in July 2021. In addition, through the difficulties associated with Covid-19, the business continued to grow. 2019 2020 2021 LTM May 2021 FY 2022 FY Car Wash $ 39,422,843 52,271,117 63,023,387 74,707,232 134,211,780 Detail 2,980,699 2,637,284 2,882,480 3,088,915 3,358,223 Convenience Store 3,853,268 4,414,443 4,636,526 4,820,252 4,972,916 Fuel 22,068,835 17,252,622 18,863,999 18,863,999 18,863,999 Lube 1,517,721 1,476,278 1,536,337 1,569,193 1,600,577 Management Fees 2,603,820 3,072,423 3,661,607 3,788,728 4,763,292 Other 1,580,898 2,660,859 2,682,296 2,452,297 2,601,423 Revenue 74,028,083 83,785,027 97,286,633 109,290,616 170,372,210 Car Wash 3,813,370 3,789,407 4,306,288 5,005,054 9,741,964 Detail 214,719 178,508 166,721 168,199 178,152 Convenience Store 2,919,619 3,154,185 3,353,798 3,483,6"
