        "page": "200",
        "text": "EBITDA Adjustments Four areas of adjustment were made to Super Star's 2021 LTM EBITDA. These adjustments include elimination of losses for newly opened sites, non-recurring legal fees, organization! transaction costs, and PPP proceeds booked to miscellaneous income. New Site Adjustments \u2022 New car wash sites tend to increase operating losses as they ramp up business \u2022 To eliminate the drag that new locations bring to overall profitability, negative LTM EBITDA amounts were eliminated for Linda Vista and Melrose locations Other Adjustments \u2022 The Company incurred legal expenses at its California sites in the 2021 LTM period of $75k, which were non-recurring in nature related to an employment matter \u2022 Super Star was involved in sale-leaseback transactions in the 2021 LTM period which incurred $268k and $175k in fees at two sites, Greenfield and 40th Ave, respectively. One-time organization structure costs were also incurred of $127k \u2022 In 2020 the Company applied for and received PPP (Paycheck Protection Program) loans through the SBA. The Company later successfully applied for loan forgiveness, which was booked in December 2020 to miscellaneous income ($515k). An adjustment has been made removing this additional income from EBITDA consideration Previous Year Adjustments In addition to adjustments similar in nature to the above, in 2019 and 2020 Income from Subsidiaries of $4.8 mm and $12.8 mm, respectively, were also excluded to arrive at EBITDA. These represent intercompany amounts consisting of Super Star net income allocated toss Holdings after allocations to other investors. Note on Corporate Allocations Each site (except for new sites with recent openings) is charged a management fee for corporate overhead. Overhead expenses include rent for the corporate facility, professional fees, and management salaries, and totaled -=$3.5 mm in 2021 LTM. Management anticipates corporate expenses as a % of consolidated revenue will decrease overtime, since current corporate levels should generally support overall operations for the near future. Strictly Private and Confidential EBITDA Adjustments 2021 LTM EBITDA, Pre-Adjusted 31,490,753 New Site Profit Loss Elimination Linda Vista 219,386 Melrose 119,548 Subtotal 338,934 Other Adjustments Non-Recurring Legal 75,053 Organization / Transaction Costs 570,436 PPP Proceeds Booked to Income (515,200) Total Adjustments 469,223 "
