        "text": "ADDENDUM \u2014 Recently Financed / Private Equity Transactions About Mister Car Wash LEONARD GREEN Founded in 1996, Mister Car Wash (\"MCW\" or the \"Company\") is the largest and fastest growing car wash chain in the United States with over 300+ locations, thirty-two (32) Oil Change Express centers, and more than 7,500 employees. The Company's growth has been fueled by innovative technology, valued customers and investors and most importantly, motivated employees. The MCW brand is anchored in quality, speed, and customer care, allowing MCW to develop a reputation for providing high quality service at an affordable price. Innovative programs, such as the subscription-based Unlimited Wash Club, further increase customer value and enhance the customer experience. The Company focuses on the conveyor wash segment and washes over forty-five (45) million cars annually. Transaction Overview / History In 2007, UNCAP (the middle market private equity platform of Onex \u2014 one of the oldest and most successful private equity firms in North America with approximately $22B of assets under management, including $68 of Onex capital in private equity and credit securities) acquired majority interest in MCW. UNCAP helped to transform the Company from a small regional operator with geographic concentration in Houston into a market leader with over 180 locations operating in fourteen (14) states and generating more than $40MM of EBITDA. In August 2014, Leonard Green and Partners purchased the Company, generating a total of $458MM in realized proceeds to UNCAP, which represented a 7.6x gross multiple of capital invested and a 34.6% gross IRR over the seven-year investment period according to representatives from ONCAP. In 2019, Penfund (an independent provider of junior capital to North American middle market companies), announced the completion of a follow-on investment in MCW as part of a small club of lenders providing a new $225MM second lien credit facility. The proceeds of this facility, together with the proceeds of a new $800MM first lien term loan, have been used to refinance MCW's existing debt and to pay a distribution to shareholders. Senior lenders also provided a new $75MM revolving credit facility and $40MM delayed draw term loan. Mister Car Wash (NYSE: MCW) made its public debut in June 2021, raising $468MM as shares quickly rallied to 49% above the IPO price of $15 per s"
