        "page": "222",
        "text": "SPONSORSHIP / MANAGEMENT OVERVIEW (Cont.) l Russell Speeder's Mr. Shullman's successful career in the car wash industry began in 1984, when he served as co-owner of Detail Plus with his brother while attending Pace University (BA.). Upon graduation, Mr. Shullman took over management of Express Car Wash of Delray, where he was able to apply the management lessons he learned in college. Under his leadership, annual sales at the location grew from $425,000 to $840,000 within two (2) years through enhanced operating tactics and improved marketing strategies. In 1997, Mr. Shullman developed an automatic wheel-cleaning machine in use at all Express locations, which reduced processing time by 40% and labor costs by $25,000 per store per year. In recent years, Mr. Shullman has been responsible for Russell Speeder's Connecticut, Nebraska, Ohio, New York, Michigan and Missouri locations. A highly experienced operator and manager, Mr. Shullman has also expanded the firm's business to include management services, which the firm provides to other car wash owners seeking his operations skillset and prowess. Today, the Russell Speeder's business grosses over $48 million across twenty-three (23) locations. Over the course of his career, Mr. Shullman has invested significant time identifying and acquiring new locations, researching top-of-the-line operating techniques (as far away as Germany), and developing various marketing, operating, accounting, and human resource programs. From 2017-2020, Mr. Shullman implemented one of the most successful car wash subscription programs in the US. While most car washes either boast high subscription volumes at a low prices, or low subscription volumes at high prices, Mr. Shullman has achieved high subscription volumes at a high price through the implementation of the above-mentioned enhancements and programs. Additional Brand Overview Founded in 1907, Shell CHI Company is an international energy company with expertise in the exploration, production, refining and marketing of oil and natural gas, and the manufacturing of chemicals. Shell is the United States-based wholly owned subsidiary of Royal Dutch Shell, which is headquartered in The Hague, the Netherlands. Considered one of the largest oil companies in the world, Shell has over 80,000 employees and 25,000 Shell-branded gas stations throughout approximately 70 different countries. S"
