        "page": "245",
        "text": "Overview of Valuations Ca rwashes' meteoric rise in popularity has created much confusion, uncertainty, and change in valuations over the past five years. For decades prior to the recent boom, performing carwashes traded at relatively stable and predictable, albeit largely more opaque from an external investors lens, levels. Historically, carwashes have traded for 4- 6x EWEBITDA multiples (inclusive of real estate). Throughout the past half a decade, several factors have come into play that have caused radical shifts and changes in valuations. Main events and influencers include the going public of Mister Car Wash and Driven Brands, the general boon of institutional investor group and fund involvement in the space, and the proliferation of sale-leasebacks throughout the industry. For an industry that has largely been ignored by the general investing public, the level of increased interest and newly founded external party demanded desire for clarity in \"appropriate\" multiples and valuations, has created an abundance of misinformation and a lacking general consensus as to answers concerning valuations. Visual Valuation Construct Measured by number of sites transacted Private Market Car Wash Valuations by Year (Trading 12 months EV/Adj. EBITDA) 10x 9x10x 10x ax 7x 9x Bx dill 11111 Ili!! 11111 2019 2020 2021 2022 2023 1111-3 Sites Mmn \u20221-3 Sites Max \u2022 3-20 Sites Min \u20223-20 Sites Max \u2022 20. Sites Min www.carwashadvisory.com 21"
